The White House, together with the Department of State and the Department of Commerce, will host the Presidential Summit on Entrepreneurship in Washington, D.C. on April 26 and 27. The summit aims to highlight the role of entrepreneurship in addressing common challenges and building partnerships for greater opportunity. It was announced by President Obama during his June 4, 2009 speech in Cairo as a way to deepen ties between business leaders, foundations, and entrepreneurs in the United States and Muslim communities worldwide. Participants from over 40 countries on 5 continents have been invited to participate.